properties.sfomuseum:description: Airmail flight cover, part of International Tributes to the History of Flight series by the Postal Commemorative Society; white envelope with full color illustration cachet and inset stamp commemorating first solo flight around the world on July 15, 1933, at Flatbush Station, New York, U.S.A., by Wiley Post with Lockheed Vega monoplane; cancellation stamp dated July 15, 1984 in Flatbush Station; includes information on reverse.
